Project Overview
This project is a File-Driven Data Processing Application developed using Python. It reads sales data from an external CSV file and processes it to generate useful insights such as total sales, average sales, and highest/lowest sales.
The program uses Python’s built-in external modules to efficiently handle file operations and perform data analysis. It simulates a real-world data processing system where information is stored externally and processed dynamically.

Objectives
Understand file-driven application development
Work with CSV files for data storage
Use external Python modules
Perform data analysis and generate reports
Build a menu-driven system

Tools & Technologies
Python 3
VS Code / IDLE
CSV file (sales.csv)

External Modules Used
csv → for reading data from files
os → for file checking
statistics → for calculating average

Project Description

The application reads sales data stored in a CSV file. Each record contains:
Product Name
Quantity Sold
Price per Unit

The program processes this data and provides:
Total sales amount
Average sales value
Highest sale
Lowest sale

The system is menu-driven, allowing users to select different operations and view results interactively.

